Ayobami Oluwagbenga, (27), was on Wednesday remanded in Nigerian Correctional Center, Ile-Ife over alleged attempt to strangulate one Insp. Akinpelu OlaOluwa thereby causing injury on the neck of the victim. The police prosecutor, Inspector Sunday Osanyintuyi, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on Feb 2, 2020 around 06:30 am at KOPEK Construction Company, Alakowe along Ilesa road, Ile-Ife. Osanyintuyi said that the defendant also threatened to kill one Ayodele Kehinde with a knife. He added that the defendant assaulted Inspector Akinpelu OlaOluwa by attempting to strangulate and choke him thereby causing him to injury on his neck. Besides, according to Olaoluwa, the defendant used knife to stab Ayodele Kehinde, on his stomach. He added that the defendant unlawfully damaged Chinese Police handcuff valued N7,000, property of Inspector Akinpelu OlaOluwa. The Prosecutor stated further that the offence contravened sections 86, 356 and 451 of the Criminal Code, Laws of Osun,  2002. The defendant however, pleaded not guilty to the four-count charge of threats to life, stabbing, assault and damaging levelled against him. Magistrate Habibat Basiru refused the bail of the defendant, but ordered that he be remanded in Ile-Ife Nigerian Correctional Centre as she adjourned the case until Feb 20, for hearing. 